<h3>Admission & Application Information - MSBM &amp; MBA</h3>
<p>For more detailed information, see the College of Graduate Studies page.</p>
<p>The Master's in Sport Business Management (MSBM) Program is full-time and consists of a cohort group of approximately 25 to 32 students who complete the program in five consecutive semesters. Courses will start either at 7:30 a.m.  or 10:30 a.m. and last three hours each Monday through Friday. This program DOES NOT offer evening or online courses. There will also be a three credit hour internship which will be in the last semester of the program, please see Curriculum and Course Requirements for more details.</p>
<p>Students must complete 42 hours of community service per semester with the exception of the summer and internship semester. Assistance in obtaining internships and community service will be provided by the program. Students are also encouraged to attend conferences and events; in addition, they are expected to coordinate events while in the program such as the Alumni Brunch and Family Weekend. For a list of attended conferences, please Networking Opportunities until DeVos Student Resources.</p>
<p>Students in the Sport Business Management Program have the opportunity to apply to the MBA program and, if accepted, also receive an MBA. If accepted, they will earn this second degree upon successful completion of two additional graduate courses (six credit hours). In the class of 2013, all 28 students graduated received their MBA when they walked in graduation in December 2012, and all 28 will receive their MSBM in May 2013 after completion of their internships.</p>
<p>Applications are accepted throughout the year. However, admission will only be granted in the fall for this specialized program.</p>

